rComments: If you want an A+, you definitely have to work for it but you will be rewarded nicely if you do the work. Also, PARTICIPATION is a key component of the course, it's not a slacker course. The prof is very nice, respectful, caring, and always willing to give extension to submit the homework and assignments if you ask for it.

This class made me grow white hair from the anxiety it gave me, but the prof is really nice. He is caring and corrects mistakes very gently. I recommend this class if you're not an anxious person like me, since participation is a key component of this class.
This course requires some effort, but the prof explains the material very well and answers questions in a very clear manner

Easy course even if you're not familiar with Arabic. It requires some practice; class notes and activities provide enough practice. It could be very boring and useless if you're familiar with the language. The prof is very easy to talk to and is very understanding and very flexible. Highly recommended : )
If you show up to TLBs, oral will be easy. Easily accessible during office hours. Definitely recommended : )
Very patient and correct grammar errors perfectly. Highly recommended
